{"questionId":"21325","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The Voronoi diagram below shows three identical cellular phone towers, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>T</mtext><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>T</mtext><mn>2</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>T</mtext><mn>3</mn></math>.&nbsp;A fourth identical cellular phone tower, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>T</mtext><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp;is located in the shaded region. The dashed lines in the&nbsp;diagram below represent the edges in the Voronoi diagram.</p>\n<p>Horizontal scale: <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math> unit represents <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>km</mtext></math>.<br>Vertical scale: <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;unit represents&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>km</mtext></math>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/7ac9c27733d36485d3c05f79490cb0365a5b8612.png\"></p>\n<p>Tim stands inside the shaded region.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Tower <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>T2</mtext></math> has coordinates <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and the edge connecting vertices <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math> has&nbsp;equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the coordinates of tower&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>T4</mtext></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for each correct coordinate. Award at most <em><strong>A0A1</strong></em> if parentheses are missing.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;<em><strong><br>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21325","referenceCode":"21M.1.SL.TZ1.5b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the coordinates of tower T4.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.6—Voronoi diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}